            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Start with profit before tax, add back non-cash items such as depreciation, adjust for working capital movements, then split the result into operating, investing and financing activities. Profit before tax of Rs 30 lakh with Rs 5 lakh depreciation and a Rs 8 lakh rise in receivables gives Rs 27 lakh of operating cash before tax paid."
