        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the difference between a cash flow statement and a fund flow statement?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "A cash flow statement tracks actual cash and cash equivalents moving in and out across operating, investing and financing activities for a period. A fund flow statement tracks changes in working capital and in long-term sources and uses between two balance sheet dates. Cash flow forms part of statutory financial statements, while fund flow is only a management tool."
          }
